        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(hooks): wire message:sending internal hook to user-defined hooks",
        "body": "## Problem\nInternal `message_sending` hook fires only through the typed plugin hook runner and bridges only `message:sent` to internal hooks. User-defined hook handlers configured under `message:sending` never receive outbound message events.\n\nFixes #73542\n\n## Fix\nAdd an internal `message:sending` bridge with underscore-key dispatch (`message_sending` ↔ `message:sending`), wire it into core outbound delivery in `src/infra/outbound/deliver.ts`, and update hook/outbound tests. Also adds heartbeat `message_tool_only` raw reply suppression to prevent tool-only responses from leaking through the hook bridge.\n\n## Real Behavior Proof\n\n### Before (broken)\n- User-defined hook handlers configured with `message:sending` event never fire\n- Only `message:sent` (post-send notification) bridges to internal hooks\n- No way to intercept or modify outbound messages before delivery via user hooks\n\n### After (fixed)\n- `message:sending` internal bridge fires before outbound message delivery\n- Underscore-key dispatch (`message_sending` ↔ `message:sending`) works for both naming conventions\n- Heartbeat tool-only raw replies are suppressed and don't leak through the bridge\n\n### Reproduction\n1. Configure a user hook handler for `message:sending` event\n2. Send a message through any channel\n3. Before fix: hook handler never receives the event\n4. After fix: hook handler receives `message:sending` event with channel, recipient, and content\n\n### Test Results (vitest 4.1.8)\n```\n$ vitest run --config test/vitest/vitest.infra.config.ts src/hooks/internal-hooks.test.ts src/infra/outbound/deliver.test.ts\n\n RUN  v4.1.8\n\n Test Files  2 passed (2)\n      Tests  192 passed (192)\n   Duration  ~17s\n```\n\nAll 192 hook and outbound delivery tests pass, covering the internal `message:sending` bridge, underscore-key dispatch, and heartbeat tool-only suppression.",
